      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROYAL ACCOLADE (7) is hard to knock on his recent form, finishing 3L of the winner last time out in a CL5 at Esperance. Right down in the weights here and Faithfull hops on board. Can sit close to the speed today and can get back to winning ways. PLAY DICE (5) sat on the speed last start and got the job done over 1230m. Back to 1100m today may be a niggle, though she should be close to the speed once again from the draw and she can repeat the dose. SIR DREAMALOT (2) makes his return in much easier company today and resumes without a trial under his belt. Riordan's claim and the inside barrier is a big tick. Can make a statement on his return. HEAD'EM (6) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back to his best form. OXBRIDGE (1) is the class runner of this field and can't be discounted despite the massive weight he carries.",
